<title>HONG KONG: Yanion Int'l 1996 net down 63 percent.</title>
<headline>Yanion Int'l 1996 net down 63 percent.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-05-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended December 31</p>
<p>(in million HK$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (H.K. cents)	   8.2	 vs 22.0</p>
<p>    Dividend (H.K. cents)    2.0	 vs 2.0</p>
<p>    Exceptional items	  7.85 loss vs 4.54 loss</p>
<p>    Net			    7.95	vs 21.33</p>
<p>    Turnover		     390.67    vs 498.09</p>
<p>    Company name		 Yanion International Holdings Ltd</p>
<p>    Books close		  June 23-26</p>
<p>    Dividend payable	   July 18</p>
<p>NOTE - Yanion International makes cassette drives, metal and plastic components and metal moulds.</p>
<p>Net is after an exceptional loss on provision for doubtful debts.</p>
<p>Total dividend for year is two H.K. cents vs same.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6368</p>
